    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>WORK PLACE MATERNITY RIGHTS PACT</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Elizabeth Olson</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Olson, Elizabeth</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>International Labor Organization adopts pact that strengthens rights of women workers; accord extends maternity leaves from 12 to 14 weeks, guarantees women right to same jobs after their leaves, bars pregnancy tests for job applicants and strengthens breast feeding provisions (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>A pact was adopted by the International Labor Organization to upgrade a 1952 treaty that strengthens the rights of women workers. The agreement extends maternity leave from 12 to 14 weeks, guarantees women the right to the same jobs after their leaves, bars pregnancy tests for job applicants and strengthens provisions for breast feeding.</p>
        <p>Elizabeth Olson</p>
      </block>
